    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-02-02T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-02-02T18:00:00-05:00" n="30"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.797/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-02-02T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 2, 1927—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Department understands from your telegrams No. 2, January 25, 3 p.m., and
                    January 29, 4 p.m., your despatch No. 45, January 12 and Consulate’s report of
                    January 13<note n="5" xml:id="d30fn5">Despatch and consulate’s report not
                        printed.</note> that proposed contract is for <pb facs="0123" n="21"
                        xml:id="pg_21"/> an exclusive franchise for tram-lines and bus-lines on
                    certain specified routes. To this as well as to customs exemptions granted by
                    contract the Department would not object. Should the contract, however, go
                    further than this and in effect restrict freedom of competition to such a degree
                    as to result in the virtual exclusion of American automotive products from a
                    particular market, you should predicate upon such exclusion appropriate
                    representations to the Greek Government pointing out that in granting the
                    concession the Greek Government is in fact consenting to discrimination against
                    American commerce. You may, in your discretion, state orally that such
                    discrimination would be viewed with concern by your Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
